This project implements an advanced trading execution system based on the research paper "A reinforcement learning extension to the Almgren-Chriss framework for optimal trade execution" by Hendricks and Wilcox. The system combines traditional algorithmic trading methods with machine learning to optimize trading performance.

This project involves building a web application for detecting fake reviews using machine learning. The application is developed using Django as the web framework, SQLite as the database, and HTML, CSS, and JavaScript for the frontend. Machine learning models are integrated to predict whether a review is fake or real based on the textual data.
